{{Other uses|Thyestes (disambiguation)}}
'''''Thyestes''''' ({{lang-grc|Θυέστης}}) is a lost tragedy by [[Euripides]].  The play may have concerned the myth of [[Thyestes]]' seduction of [[Areope]], the wife of his brother [[Atreus]], and Atreus' subsequent revenge on Thyestes, killing his children and serving them to him at a feast.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Conacher|first=D. J.|title=Review: ''The Tragedies of Euripides'' by T. B. L. Webster|year=1970|journal=Phoenix|volume=24|issue=1}}</ref>

